        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:24PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Prewitt Reservoir, or 17 miles southwest of Sterling, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merino, Prewitt Reservoir, Atwood, Messex and Fremont Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
